<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Greece "Perfect" in Military Cooperation: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Cooperation on military and
defense matters between Cyprus and Greece is "perfect", the
defense ministers of the two countries said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot Defense Minister Socrates Hasikos and his Greek
counterpart Akis Tsohatzopoulos also vowed that this cooperation
will continue. Tsohatzoupoulos is here on a four-day official
visit.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers told a press conference that Cyprus' defense
capability is at a very high standard.
</P>
<P>
On attempts to settle the Cyprus issue, Tsohatzopoulos noted
the unprecedented effort by the U.S. to help reach a settlement
but called for "great care" in dealing with any moves that may
promote other goals.
</P>
<P>
Tsohatzopoulos said both Greece and Cyprus see the prospect of
Turkey joining the European Union in a positive light provided
Ankara contributes to the peace effort and paves the way for
substantive negotiations leading to a solution in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
On defense matters the Greek minister said he was certain
Cyprus' armed forces were at the peak of their readiness and the
art of war.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers watched earlier part of the annual military
manoeuvres of Cyprus' National Guard "Nikiforos 99".
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Turkish Cypriots-controlled
north and the Greek Cypriots-dominated south since 1974 when
Turkish troops invaded and occupied the northern third of the
island in the wake of a failed coup seeking union with Athens.
</P>
<P>
Greece and Cyprus reached an agreement in November, 1993
that Greek will offer Cyprus land, sea and air cover in the
event of fresh Turkish attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
