<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 2 Others Injured in Building Collapse in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and two
others injured on Sunday when a building collapsed in Cairo,
police officials said.
</P>
<P>
Karima Mohammed el-Sayyed and her husband, Abbas Mustapha, both
66, died when their old four-story building crashed, the officials
said.
</P>
<P>
El-Sayyed's sister, Fatima, 64, was also killed. Another
sister, Sayida, 65, and their brother, Hussein, 61, were injured
when they were visiting el-Sayyed's home.
</P>
<P>
No other people were in the building, which is in the capital's
Sayida Zeinab neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
Police advised the residents in 1993 to leave the building for
fear that it might collapse, but some families did not follow the
advice.
</P>
<P>
Building collapses are common in Egypt due to shoddy
construction, poor materials or additions built without permits.
</P>
</TEXT>
