<HEADLINE> 17 Tons of Drugs Seized in Iran in Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 17 tons of narcotics were
seized in Iran's southeastern province of Kerman during the first
half of the current Iranian year starting March 21, an increase of
four tons from the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier General Abbasali Rouhi, commander of the provincial
Law Enforcement Forces (LEF) disclosed the figure in Kerman Sunday
while addressing the LEF flag hoisting ceremony in this provincial
capital city.
</P>
<P>
Drug trafficking has been rampant in the area overlapping parts
of Iran, Pakistan and Afghanistan despite anti-drug campaigns.
Drugs are being shipped from the so-called Gold Crescent to world
markets via Iran and Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
