<HEADLINE> 1 Ton of Heroin Seized in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police Sunday seized one
ton of heroin in an anti-drug operation in Turkey's eastern
province of Agri, the semi-official Anatolia news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Agri Governor Lutfi Yigenoglu said that acting on a tip-off,
the Turkish police stopped a TIR truck at Turkish-Iranian Gurbulak
Border Gate in Gogubayazit town of Agri province and found 1 ton
of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Yigenoglu said that the drugs were planted under the garlic in
the truck coming from neighboring Iran and the driver has been
arrested for questioning.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police launched 2,928 operations against
drug-trafficking last year and seized over 10 tons of narcotics,
including 5.3 tons of hashish and 3.8 tons of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs trafficking from the
border area of Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
