<HEADLINE> S. Africa Condemns New Violence in DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The South African
Government Sunday condemned "in the strongest possible terms"
cease-fire violations in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria was reacting to reports that tanks were used to attack
Rally for Congolese Democracy positions, 12 kilometers from
Kabinda, early Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by the Foreign Affairs Department, South
Africa called on the Organization of African Unity and the
chairman of the Joint Military Committee to establish who the
perpetrators of the attacks were.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria also called on all parties and signatories to the
cease-fire to put firm measures into place in order to prevent
such actions. 
</P>
