<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, October 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Violence escalated on the final phase of polling
in the 13th Lok Sabha elections Sunday as 13 people were killed in
three northeast states of Assam, Bihar and Tripura.
</P>
<P>
In Barpeta Lok Sabha constituency of Assam, militants fired
upon security men posted at a polling station in Hahchora area at
0530 hours local time, killing three police officers and two Home
Guard personnel on the spot.
</P>
<P>
In Madhepura Lok Sabha constituency of Bihar, a local RJD party
president was gunned down by supporters of another local party.
</P>
<P>
In Dhalai district of Tripura, seven people, including four
security men on poll patrol duty, were killed in an ambush by
militants.
</P>
<P>
According to PTI, incidents of snatching of ballot papers and
an attempt to disrupt the poll process were reported from certain
places in Assam. (India-Poll Violence)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli-Palestinian Safe Passage Committee is
scheduled to meet again Sunday evening to iron out differences
over the opening of the safe passage linking Gaza Strip and the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Public Security Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami said the
Committee can settle the contentious issues concerning the opening
of the passage soon.
</P>
<P>
The passage will be opened on Sunday as scheduled but due to
some differences between the two sides, its opening has been
postponed, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators met at Neveh Ilan Hotel
near Jerusalem for more than five hours Saturday evening on the
opening of the passage. (Israel-Passage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- One person was killed and about 50 others were injured
in Bangladesh on Sunday during the opposition-organized dawn-to-
dusk countrywide hartal (destructive strike).
</P>
<P>
One activist of the major opposition -- the Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) -- was gunned down in a clash between pro-
and anti-hartal activists in Sherpur district, about 150
kilometers north of here, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The three-hour battle at Sherpur town between supporters of the
opposition and anti-strike activists of the ruling Awami League
also left 20 persons injured, including one constable, a
superintendent of police was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Some 25 people were injured during the shutdown in northeastern
Netrakona town, about 140 km from Dhaka, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said some 50 opposition marchers were arrested by
police in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
The BNP-led opposition alliance, which also comprises the
Jatiya Party, the Jamaat-e-Islami and the Islami Oikya Jote (
Islamic Solidarity Front), enforced the strike to press home their
demands including the resignation of the government and early
parliamentary elections. (Bangladesh-Strike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The leading Indian TV station Doordarshan released
an exit poll Sunday night, projecting a simple majority for the
BJP-led National Democratic Alliance (NDA) with 287 seats in the
Lok Sabha elections.
</P>
<P>
The Congress and its allies were placed at 174 seats at the end
of fifth and final phase of polling.
</P>
<P>
Individually BJP was projected to bag 185 seats, three more
than it had in the 12th Lok Sabha while Congress will make a gain
of five seats to reach 146.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the Development and Research Services,
covered 34,000 voters spread over 155 Lok Sabha constituencies.
</P>
<P>
However, an exit poll conducted for marathi newspaper "Lokmat"
predicted a hung house with the BJP-led NDA getting 242 seats,
Congress 227, left front 42 and others 25.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the exit poll showed that 51 percent of those
interviewed preferred Atal Bihari Vajpayee for Prime Ministership
while 37 percent wanted Congress President Sonia Gandhi to occupy
the top slot.
</P>
<P>
The poll said that 50 percent of the people wanted the Vajpayee-
led government to be re-elected while 41 percent preferred a
change. (India-Exit Poll) 
</P>
</TEXT>
