<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The opening of a safe passage between the West
Bank and Gaza Strip has been postponed due to Israeli and
Palestinian negotiators' failure to resolve their differences in a
meeting Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Orit Messer-Harel, spokeswoman of the Israeli Public Security
Ministry said the main sticking points were which side and where
to issue the passage passes and whether Isarel is entitled to
arrest Palestinians suspected of security offenses as they use the
passage.
</P>
<P>
The passage, linking Gaza and the West Bank city of Hebron, was
supposed to be opened October 1 under the Sharm El Sheikh peace
deal signed early September. But the opening has been postponed
for two days by the Israeli side due to the Israel's Jewish
holiday. (BC-Isarel-Passage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- A Lebanese religious man was killed in a bomb
explosion Sunday in a church in east Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded at 11:50 a.m. (0850 GMT) when Shafik Rajha, a
deacon in the Saint Georges Church in the Dekwaneh area, tried to
open a handbag behind the altar. The 67-year-old deacon was killed
on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which occurred just a few minutes after a mass rally
was held in the church, also caused damage to furniture and window
panes, a security source said.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for the blast, the
first in Beirut for more than two years. And the motive behind the
explosion was not immediately known. (BC-Lebanon-Bomb Explosion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli-Palestinian Safe Passage Committee is
scheduled to meet again Sunday evening to try to iron out
differences over the opening of the southern safe passage route.
</P>
<P>
The major sticking points were which side and where to issue
the corridor passes and whether Israel is entitled to arrest
Palestinians suspected of security offenses as they use the
passage.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side wants to be the ultimate issuing authority
for the passes. Israeli newspapers reported that Israel wants to
maintain control in order to prevent forgeries by militants
planning attacks.
</P>
<P>
The southern safe passage that links Gaza and Tarkumia near the
West Bank city of Hebron was scheduled to open on October 1 under
the lastest Palestinian-Israeli peace deal, or the Sharm al-Sheikh
Memorandum. The opening date was reset for Sunday because of
Jewish holidays on Friday and Saturday. (BC-Israel-Palestine-Safe
Passage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's Interior Ministry is planning to use force to
free the three Portuguese nationals kidnapped by drug smugglers,
an official of the ministry has said.
</P>
<P>
The official said "we will use force to teach a lesson to the
drug traffickers who must stop this sort of blackmailing," the
English daily Tehran Times reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The clan called "narooi" in Iran's southeastern province of
Sistan-Baluchistan, which is notorious for drug-trafficking, was
responsible for the kidnapping. (BC-Iran-Hostages) 
