<HEADLINE> Banquet marks Sino-Bulgarian Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a banquet here
this evening to mark the 50th anniversary of the establishment of
Sino-Bulgarian diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhenghua, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), together with other senior
Chinese officials, attended the banquet.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said on the occasion that although
great changes have taken place in both the international situation
and domestic situation in the two countries over the past half a
century, Sino-Bulgarian friendship has maintained and developed
further.
</P>
<P>
He added that leaders of the two countries have also had
frequent exchanges of visits, and cooperation in various fields
has been progressing. Qi said he believed that Sino-Bulgarian
friendship and cooperation will continue to grow in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's ambassador to China Dimitar Tzanev said that
Bulgaria's governments at various periods of time have respected
the choice made by the Chinese people and China's foreign policy
of peace. He wished that the Chinese people will make even greater
progress in the years ahead. 
</P>
