<HEADLINE> Regional Meeting on Local Governance Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Uganda
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The seventh conference of the
African Union of Local Authorities (AULA) opened here Monday
morning, calling for more effective ways to improve local
governance across the continent.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which drew hundreds of participants from 17
African countries, was officially opened by Ugandan Prime Minister
Apollo Nsibambi.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this conference is Community Participation in
Local Governance in the Next Millenium.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the International Conference Center here,
President of the International Union of Local Authorities (IULA)
Max Nga'dwe said in the past decade Africa has shown unprecedented
commitment to strengthening democratic local governance.
</P>
<P>
AULA, an affiliate of IULA, was founded in 1984 following a
conference in Harare, Zimbabwe, with Challenges for Local
Governments in Africa as its theme. 
