<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index Up 2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks surged
Monday amid optimism that the long-standing power tariff dispute
between the Independent Power Producers (IPPs) and the government
could be resolved in a short term, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index of Karachi Stock Exchange closed
24.94 points, or 2.08 percent, higher to 1,223.04 from Friday's
1,198.10.
</P>
<P>
The turnover on Monday stood at 133.793 million shares against
Friday's 163.291 million shares.
</P>
<P>
There was strong optimism in the market due to the planned
meeting of Finance Minister Ishaq Dar with leaders of Hub Power
Company (Hubco), which investors expected to lead to the solution
of the tariff dispute, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
Hubco, the largest IPP with a weightage of 18 percent of the
100-share index, rose by 0.75 rupees, or 3.85 percent, to 20.25
rupees on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 183 active issues, gainers beat losers 105 to 29
while 49 remained unchanged. 
</P>
