<HEADLINE> Philippine House Speaker Urges Halt to Mindanao Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine House Speaker Manny
Villar on Monday urged military authorities as well as leaders of
the secessionist Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) to end the
fierce fighting in the southern Philippines that has left at least
67 MILF guerrillas and an undetermined number of government troops
dead.
</P>
<P>
"We have seen enough dead Filipinos," Villar said, as he urged
a resolution to the ongoing conflict. He appealed to the MILF to
"sit down and dialogue" with the government instead of resorting
to armed responses, Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The source of the conflict, military officials claim, is the
MILF's harassment of military patrols in an attempt to expand
their territory beyond Camp Omar in Cotabato, Mindanao, in
preparation for coming peace talks on October 25.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, on the other hand, says that it was the military that
intruded into their territory.
</P>
<P>
"It's ironic that while peace talks are set for this month,
fighting is still going on," Villar said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the commitment of the House of Representatives to
bringing forth a lasting peace throughout the country, especially
in the Mindanao region.
</P>
<P>
"Mindanao's potential as a growth area will only be put to
waste if peace and stability cannot be achieved in the region,"
Villar said.
</P>
<P>
"We are doing our best to help the government find a lasting
peace solution that will hopefully begin a new era of development
in Mindanao," he said, as he urged MILF leaders "to keep an open
mind" and believe in the sincerity of the administration to end
the secessionist problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
