<HEADLINE> First Chinese McDonnell-Douglas Airliner Passes Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The first large MD-90 airliner
manufactured by Chinese in cooperation with the U.S. company
completed its first test flight on Sunday in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The 3-hour flight carried 10 Chinese and U.S. aviation experts.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft can carry as many as 165 passengers and has a
range of 4,020 km. About 70 percent of the airliner's components
were produced locally and represent a major improvement in Chinese
aviation engineering and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Its electronics and equipment make the aircraft fuel efficient
and relatively quiet, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
China's leading aircraft manufacturers in cities like Shanghai,
Chengdu, Xi'an, and Shenyang have been involved in the project,
which began in 1995. Analysts say that manufacturers will apply to
government departments in the United States to extend their
licensing agreements soon after they finish the second trial
flight, so that the aircraft will be fully eligible for commercial
use. 
</P>
