<HEADLINE> President Agrees to Establishment of NATO Bases in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Since Bulgaria has, for two and a half years, constantly
reiterated its willingness to become a member of NATO, the country
should also share NATO's responsibilities. If the question of
setting up bases is raised with us, I shall say 'yes'," said the
president, further conforming his statement made on September 22.
</P>
<P>
One week after Stoyanov's statement, Russian Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said that the Bulgarian president's
statement was not conducive to the promotion of security and
stability in Southeastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on the Russian foreign minister's
response to the issue, the president said that Bulgaria is no
longer a member of the Warsaw Pact and can make any decision as a
sovereign country at its own discretion. 
</P>
