<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Exchange Reopens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Exchange (CSE)
reopened Monday after a one-month closure.
</P>
<P>
The CSE had been closed since September 3 according to a
decision by its board to give brokers time to clear the backlog of
transaction due to unprecedented volume of transactions over the
previous weeks.
</P>
<P>
The CSE General Index closed at 425.35 points Monday, up 1.2
percent from the closing figure on September 3.
</P>
<P>
Monday's volume of transactions was 6.9 million Cyprus pounds
(12.4 million U.S. dollars) compared to 54.1 million pounds (97.4
million dollars) on September 3. 
</P>
