<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Stakeholders attending the
Southern African International Dialogue (SAID) conference in
Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe, Monday identified the tourism sector as
the most critical area for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
SAID spokesman Mike Ndudzo said this was because the tourism
sector required less input but had the potential to offer maximum
returns on investment, Zimbabwe News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
