government, agreed to form a regional task force to assess how
cooperation could be achieved.
</P>
<P>
Ndudzo said it was agreed that legislation which hindered free
movement of people and tourists should be removed.
</P>
<P>
He said the participants felt that the development of tourism
would lead to the creation of the much needed employment for local
people.
</P>
<P>
"We felt that our priority by now is to create the jobs and
that could only be done when we develop our tourism sector," he
said. 
