<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong External Trade Increases in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The volume of total exports of
Hong Kong increased by 7.0 percent over a year earlier in July
1999, while the volume of imports increased by 7.3 percent,
according to the Census and Statistics Department of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region Monday.
</P>
<P>
Comparing to the same period of 1998, the volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports increased by 9.8 percent and that of domestic exports
fell by 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The change in volume of trade is derived from the change in
trade value with the effect of price changes discounted.
</P>
<P>
The prices of re-exports and domestic exports of July 1999 fell
by 2.6 percent and 2.5 percent respectively from those of July
1998, and at the same time import prices also declined by 2.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Analyzed by end-use category, year-on-year increases in re-
export volume in July 1999 were recorded for capital goods, raw
materials and semi-manufactures and consumer goods.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, year-on-year decreases in re-export volume
were recorded for fuels and foodstuffs.
</P>
<P>
Comparing July 1999 with July 1998, notable decreases in the
volume of domestic exports were recorded for watches and clocks,
radios, metal manufactures and travel goods.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, notable increases in the volume of domestic
exports were recorded for footwear and textile made-ups and
related articles.
</P>
<P>
Notable increases in import volume were recorded for fish and
fish preparations, and vegetables. Significant decreases were
recorded in the import volume of soya bean oil, peanut oil,
vegetable oil and lard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
