<HEADLINE> Eighth SAF Games Concluds in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 4 (Xinhua ) -- The 8th South Asian
Federation Games (SAFG) concluded here Monday.
</P>
<P>
After 10 days of competition, India won 102 gold medals,
followed by Nepal with 30 gold medals. For other participating
countries, Sri Lanka won 16 gold medals, Pakistan 10, Bangladesh
two, Bhutan one and Maldives no gold medals.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,069 athletes from the 7 SAARC countries
participated in the games, competing for 532 medals including 161
gold medals in 12 sports of football, boxing, volleyball,
wrestling, kabbadi, table tennis, swimming, shooting, aphletics,
weightlifting, taekwando and judo.
</P>
<P>
The 9th SAF Games will be held in Pakistan in 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
