<HEADLINE> Urgent: Barak Urges Assad to Advance Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak on Monday urged Syrian President Hafez al-Assad to move the
Israeli-Syrian peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
"The door of opportunity is opened today and let us make
painful decisions to solve the problems between Israel and
Syria," Barak said in his policy address to the Knesset
(parliament) which opened its winter session after a two-month
summer recession. 
