<HEADLINE> New Waterfront Start for 2000 Hong Kong Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong international
marathon, one of Asia's premier sporting events, returns with a
new waterfront start next year, said the tournament organizers
here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Amateur Athletic Association (HKAAA), the
organizer, said it would be the largest participatory running
event in Hong Kong, attracting nearly 7,000 runners from around
the world.
</P>
<P>
The tournament, which had different waterfront start in the
past three years, will begin in the shadow of the Hong Kong
Cultural Center, Tsim Sha Tsui, and will showcase some of Hong
Kong's most famous landmarks along the route next year.
</P>
<P>
The 2000 event, to be held on February 20, 2000, features three
separate competitions: a full-marathon, a half-marathon and the
popular 10 km race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
