<HEADLINE> Conference on Mass Destruction Weapons Due in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia is due to host
the first Gulf conference on the prevention of mass destruction
weapons on October 18-20.
</P>
<P>
Attending the conference will be experts and firms from
Britain, Canada, the Czech Republic, France, Germany, the
Netherlands, Russia, the United States, as well as the Gulf Arab
countries.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Bin Nasser Al-Saffar, head of the Department of the
Prevention of Mass Destruction Weapons of the Saudi Defense
Ministry, said the conference will discuss current research and
technological advancement of mass destruction weapons, as well as
ways to eliminate them and deal with their victims.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be sponsored by the Dhahran-based
Intermediate Military Health Academy, the Saudi official was
quoted by the Kuwait News Agency as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
