<HEADLINE> 154 Killed in India's Poll-Related Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 154 people were
killed in the five phases of polling in the 13th Lok Sabha
elections, which concluded Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures released by the Home Ministry
Monday, in the 1998 and 1996 elections, 251 and 313 people were
killed respectively.
</P>
<P>
Despite the deployment of 400,000 central security forces,
incidents of poll-related violence numbered 924 this year, which
was considerably less than 1,541 in 1998 and 1,209 in 1996
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the central security forces, some 470,000 home
guards were deployed for election duty and the service of 50,000
personnel of the National Cadet Corps were also availed.
</P>
<P>
Arrangements for sharing and inter-state deployment of 110,000
state security personnel among various states were also organized
by the Home Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
