<HEADLINE> Sensex Down on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive Index (SENSEX)
fell 47.59 points Monday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) in the
wake of heavy bull liquidation and absence of foreign
institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index, firm at the outset, later
moved downwards to close at its intra-day low of 4,654.72 points
as against last Friday's close of 4,702.31, netting a loss of
47.59 points or 1.01 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 Index eased by 15.78 points to 2,155.97 from
previous close of 2,171.75.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 Index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably down at
497.39 and 190.02 points compared with last weekend close of
501.04 and 191.37 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 Index moved down by 10.66 points to 1,478.52 from
previous close of 1,489.18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
