<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Announces Stamp Issuing Program for 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Post announced
details of the stamp issuing program for 2000 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Allan Chiang, acting postmaster general of Hong Kong, said the
Year 2000 program would be particularly appealing to stamp
collectors.
</P>
<P>
"For the first time, we will be issuing 22-karat gold stamps,
imperforated sheets and triangular stamps," said Chiang.
</P>
<P>
The issuing program will comprise seven special stamp issues,
four stamp sheetlets and two prestige stamp booklets.
</P>
<P>
The highlights of the program include the 22-karat gold stamp,
and stamps on the millennium, the "year of the dragon," "Hong Kong
Insects," and the "2000 Olympic Games." 
</P>
</TEXT>
