<HEADLINE> Burundi Peace Talks Delayed Due to Nyerere's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A new round of separate
consultations among warring Burundian parties, scheduled on Monday
here, has been postponed to a later date due to the critical
condition of Julius Nyerere, the mediator of Burundi peace
process.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian newspaper quoted reliable sources as saying that a
new date will be set pending the improvement of Nyerere who is
being treated for leukemia in a London hospital.
</P>
<P>
"We have been forced to postpone the separate consultations due
to the current health of Mwalimu Nyerere until further notice,"
said Judge Mark Bomani, a senior Nyerere's aide, in London.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere, 77, Tanzanian founding president, was admitted to St
Thomas Hospital for Leukemia two week ago and still remained in
the intensive care unit.
</P>
<P>
Millions of Tanzanians and foreign leaders have since prayed
for his early recovery and safe return home.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, a tentative schedule of the adjourned consultations
indicated that Burundian delegates were to arrive in Dar es Salaam
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The separate consultations are to be headed by Nyerere's two
aides, Judge Mark Bomani and Brigadier Hashim Mbita.
</P>
<P>
Both Mbita and Bomani also chaired the last round of peace
negotiations held in Arusha from September 13 to 17 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
