<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks End Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 142.62
points, or 1.12 percent, to finish Monday's session at 12,875.86.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market believed that the chance of a U.S.
interest-rate rise in the short term had dominated.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 6.807 billion HK dollars (872 million U.S.
dollars), 249 million HK dollars (32 million U.S. dollars) lower
than Thursday's turnover of 7.056 billion HK dollars (904 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and Industry
enjoyed increases of 1.69 percent, 1.90 percent, 0.13 percent and
0.14 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 1.52 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index down 2.05 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index dropped 1.92 points, or 0.02 percent, to
open at 12,731.32 Monday and went up 178.03 points to close Monday
's morning session at 12,911.27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
