<HEADLINE> Telecom Exchanges Booming Between Macao, Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- With Macao's upcoming return to
the motherland, the amount of telecommunications services between
the region and the interior areas of China is booming.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of the year, the amount of telecom
business between Macao and the mainland approached 3.5 million
times each month on the average, according to the Macao
Telecommunications Company, which enjoys the franchise in local
telecom business.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from the company show that from January to
June this year there were 1.86 million calls from Macao to the
mainland per month on the average, and 1.61 million calls the
other way round.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the monthly calls from Macao to neighboring
Guangdong Province in south China were 1.4 million times. There
are two optical telecom lines between Macao and Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the company said that the capacity of telecom
service between Macao the mainland areas of China will increase 39
percent by the year end, and long-distance calls to leading
Chinese cities will become easier and cheaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
