<HEADLINE> APLF '99 Autumn Show Attracts Over 500 Exhibitors to HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 exhibitors from
22 countries and regions around the world are displaying their
latest products and designs for 2000 Spring/Summer season at the
just opened Asia Pacific Leather Fair '99 Fashion &AMP; Finished
Products -- Autumn Show.
</P>
<P>
The show, organized by the Asia Pacific Leather Fair (APLF) Ltd.
, opened Monday morning at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center and will run until October 6.
</P>
<P>
The show has attracted a total of 535 exhibitors from various
countries and regions, including Australia, Bangladesh, Belgium,
Canada, China's mainland, France, Germany, Hong Kong, India,
Indonesia, Italy, Japan, Malaysia, Portugal, Singapore, South
Korea, Spain, Sweden, Taiwan, Thailand, the United States and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The colorful array of products is presented in four sectors:
Footwear, Garments, Finished Goods and Accessories &AMP; Components.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Pacific Leather Fair Fashion &AMP; Finished Products Show
is Asia's most important trade forum for the leather industry,
running twice a year, in spring and autumn in Hong Kong in
accordance with the fashion calendar.
</P>
<P>
The next Fashion &AMP; Finished Products -- Spring Show will be
staged from March 30 to April 1, 2000 and the Autumn Show will run
from October 25-27, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Michael Duck, general manager of APLF Ltd., said that in 2000,
the dates of the autumn show are moved towards the end of October
which follows the international leather calendar to guarantee the
best and most convenient timing for both exhibitors and visitors.
</P>
<P>
It also coincides with the Chinese Export Commodities Fair --
Autumn Fair in Guangzhou. Overseas buyers can attend these two
very important events by making one trip to Asia, Duck said.
</P>
</TEXT>
