<HEADLINE> Jordanian King Foresees Closer Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin
Hussein said Monday he foresees further development in bilateral
relations between Jordan and China, particularly in trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during meeting with Chinese Ambassador to
Jordan Qiu Shengyun when he presented the state credentials to the
Jordanian ruler at the royal palace in Amman.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Qiu conveyed to Abdullah Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's sincere greetings, saying President Jiang hoped the king
will visit China at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said he plans to visit China by the end of the year,
expressing belief that the upcoming visit would further promote
friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He recalled the three visits he had paid to China before
assuming the throne in February and said he was deeply impressed
by the rapid development and beautiful natural scenery of China.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for further development of
Sino-Jordanian relations, particularly in bilateral trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Sino-Jordanian trade volume stands at some 100
million U.S. dollars a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
