<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Formulate Policy to Check Weaponization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Interior Ministry
will soon formulate a comprehensive policy to effectively check
the race of weaponization in the country.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Shujat Hussain, while presiding over a
high-level meeting to review the prevailing law and order
situation, said here Monday that all out efforts are being made to
put an end to the weapons race.
</P>
<P>
He instructed the concerned officials from all the four
provinces to submit report within a week so that a uniform policy
to curb the menace be formulated.
</P>
<P>
The interior minister underlined the need to take the country's
intelligentsia and religious scholars into confidence to check the
gripping wave of sectarian violence in the country.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed the government's resolve to take stringent
measures against those elements who ventured to take law in their
hands.
</P>
<P>
The minister also warned that the government will not allow
such persons to succeed in their nefarious designs and those found
guilty of perpetrating violence would be accorded exemplary
punishment.
</P>
<P>
Sectarian violence occurred recent days in various parts of
Pakistan. As a result, more than 20 people were killed last week.
</P>
</TEXT>
