<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 4 (Xinhua) --The Australian sharemarket
slipped lower Monday as investors await possible interest rate
rises after meetings of both Australia's and the United States'
central banks later this week.
</P>
<P>
The Labor Day holiday was another factor which led to fairly
low volumes in the local market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index fell 17.4 points to close at
2895.5.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index dropped 25.6 points to 4957.4, while
the all resources index closed 12.9 points lower at 1303.5.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 245.20 million worth 268.73 million
U.S. dollars, with 473 falls outpacing 373 rises and 328 stocks
steady.
</P>
<P>
News Corp closed 13.6 cents lower at 7.07 U.S. dollars, with
its preferred scrip down 16.3 cents at 6.59 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telstra, the biggest communications company in Australia, added
0.1 of a cent to close at 5.26 U.S. dollars but Cable &AMP; Wireless
Optus dipped 3.3 cents to 2.14 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among resource stocks, the big miner BHP fell 28.6 cents to
11.64 U.S. dollars, fellow giant Rio Tinto dropped 30 cents to
17.22 U.S. dollars and WMC lost 10 cents to 5.04 U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
