<HEADLINE> Shares Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
Singapore Stock Market Monday as trading became more cautious
after Friday's losses on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) fell by 13.39 points,
0r 0.7 percent, to end at 2037.87 points in light dealings.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover shrank to 91.26 million units valued at 225.61
million Singapore dollars (about 132.71 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 158 to 113 with 177 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Gen Int continued to top the volume list with 18.27 million
units changing hands. Sunway was the second with 7.48 million
stocks done. Singtel was the next with a turnover of 7.19 million
counters.
</P>
<P>
ICS led the ascent of the day climbing by 151 cents to close at
5.75 Singapore dollars. SPH gained 50 cents to finish at 27.50
Singapore dollars. Seaview picked up 30 cents to end at 11.00
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS was the biggest loser of the day incurring
a loss of 70 cents to close at 18.60 Singapore dollars. UOB F sank
30 cents to finish at 13.00 Singapore dollars. CityDev retreated
25 cents to end at 8.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said many players stayed away ahead of the meeting on
Tuesday of the U.S. Federal Reserve Board.
</P>
<P>
They also said that the market traded sideways with sentiment
dampened by uncertainties over a possible U.S. interest rate hike.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
