<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Form National Housing Authority: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will form a National
Housing Authority soon to expand residential facilities across the
country, particularly for the underprivileged people, Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The government would also set up planned townships in all
district headquarters to reduce the population pressure on the
capital and big cities besides establishing a "New Dhaka City" by
2020, the prime minister said while inaugurating the National
Habitat Day '99 at the Osmani Auditorium in the capital.
</P>
<P>
Following excess population pressure and in the absence of
planned construction of townships, the cities have become almost
"unfit" for human habitation which would cause national disaster
at any moment, she said.
</P>
<P>
To improve civic amenities and healthy atmosphere, the
government has taken up a program to establish "semi-urban
infrastructure development project" in 22 district headquarters,
said the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Listing steps of the government for rehabilitation of landless
urban people, Hasina said the government has taken massive schemes
for providing environment-sound and healthy shelters for the slum
dwellers and other low-income groups.
</P>
<P>
Besides proving shelters, these people would also be given
vocational training and provided with soft loan for creating
self-employment opportunities, she said.
</P>
<P>
House-building loans which were largely confined to big cities
for privileged people only would be extended to the rural level to
encourage people to stay in rural areas instead of crowing in the
capital and other cities, said the prime minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
