<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills Seven in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and 28
others injured Monday morning when a double-decker bus collided
head-on with a truck near Tembi in central Greece.
</P>
<P>
The bus, which was carrying fans of a Thessaloniki first
division soccer team, veered into the opposite lane and collided
with an on-coming truck at high speed before falling into a ravine,
the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Four of the injured were in serious conditions, the news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The accident halted traffic in both directions for more than
three hours.
</P>
<P>
Greece is one of the European Union (EU) countries which is
plagued by a higher rate of traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents kill some 3,000 people and injure 30,000
others in Greece annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
