<HEADLINE> Afghan Opposition Launches Counterattack in North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's opposition
United Front Monday launched a counterattack against the dominant
Taliban militia in the northern province of Takhar, sources from
Kabul said.
</P>
<P>
The counterattack came in the wake of the recent wave of
offensives launched by the Taliban forces aimed at seizing
Taloqan, the capital of Takhar.
</P>
<P>
The opposition claimed to have managed to capture the areas of
Dasht-i-Gaza, Kahgadai and Ashti during its latest offensive,
according to the sources, who failed to give independent
confirmation.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the hard-line Islamic Taliban militia is
currently making preparations for a major offensive on Taloqan.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban have been locked in a five-year long civil war
against the northern opposition. The recent fighting in Takhar and
neighboring areas has displaced thousands of people, the
opposition claimed. 
</P>
