<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Northwestern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2
degrees on the open-ended Richter scale hit Iran's northwestern
province of Ardebil Sunday, but no reports on possible damage are
available now.
</P>
<P>
The tremor took place at 4:49 p.m. local time (1319 GMT) Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The seismological base of Tabriz, affiliated to the Geophysics
Institute of Tehran University, registered the epicenter of the
quake at the western coast of the Caspian Sea, somewhere in the
Gulf of Ilic in Azerbaijan. The quake was also felt in Moghan,
Namin regions. 
</P>
