<DOCNO> XIE19991004.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Coffee Export Sales Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's coffee export sales in
the first 11 months of the 1998-1999 crop was down 10.3 percent
from the year-ago period, Vietnam's business newspaper The Saigon
Times Daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper attributed the drop to a continuous decline in
export prices since early this year.
</P>
<P>
Figures of the Vietnam Coffee and Cocoa Association show the
country in the October-September period exported 505 million U.S.
dollars worth of coffee.
</P>
<P>
The average coffee price in the period was a mere 1,395 U.S.
dollars a ton, down from 1,525 U.S. dollars a ton in the same
period of the last crop.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam Coffee Corporation was Vietnam's biggest exporter,
though its shipments abroad in the period fell to 49,513 tons from
the 93,696 tons in the crop-ago period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
