<HEADLINE> Zambian Business Coalition on HIV/AIDS Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A Zambian business coalition on
HIV/AIDS has been set up, Zambian Daily Mail newspaper reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, outgoing advisor to United Nations Program on
HIV/AIDS (UNAIDS) country program Bernadette Olowo-Freers said all
U.N. agencies in the country would soon request the Zambian
government to integrate HIV and AIDS with the school curriculum so
that pupils and students in higher institutions of learning are
all kept abreast with latest developments in the context of this
epidemic.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the UNAIDS, a delegation comprising participants
from Zambia, Swaziland and some other African countries has
visited Thailand recently in a bid to draw lessons from the Asian
state in fighting against HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Officially launched in 1993, Thailand Business Coalition on
AIDS has been mobilizing resources (money and skills) from the
private sector for HIV/AIDS prevention and implementation of
workplace education programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
