<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Fresh Riot in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Three civilians were killed and
seven others injured in a new riot in Ambon, capital of
Indonesia's Maluku province, on Monday, according to reports
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The clash broke out after four members of the security
apparatus led a mass who burned houses in the city.
</P>
<P>
The four military personnel fired on those who wanted to
extinguish the fire that ravaged 23 houses, while the fire-brigade
was not around because of the difficult access to the area.
</P>
<P>
The gun shots and hand-made bomb explosions in Batu Merah Dalam
and Karangpanjang district are continuing, according to the Antara
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, a civilian was shot dead by unidentified people on
his way to a Chapel in Batumerah area.
</P>
<P>
Ambon and several other islands in Maluku province have been
the scene of violent clashes between Muslims and Christian groups
since mid-January this year.
</P>
<P>
Local religious figures, along with the military, had tried to
reconcile the warring camps but clashes broke out again in
mid-July, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The unrest in July claimed dozens of lives, injured an even
rnghlcw
bigger number of people and caused hundreds of residents to flee
their homes.
</P>
<P>
Most of Indonesia's 202 million people are Muslims, but Maluku
is a predominantly Christian province. 
</P>
