<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 16 in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A 75-seater bus left the
road and plunged down an embankment in East London, South Africa,
on Sunday night, killing at least 16 people and leaving 50
injured.
</P>
<P>
It was the latest bloody chapter in the country's on-going road
mayhem, the Star newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
At least 12 ambulances along with several police and fire unit
vehicles rushed to the scene of the accident.
</P>
<P>
Noel Williams, commander of the East London fire and rescue
services, said the bus driver appeared to have lost control of the
vehicle on a 90- degree bend.
</P>
<P>
The crash came only days after a meeting between the Department
of Transport and bus operators to discuss a spate of tragic
accidents over the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
It came almost a week after the death of 26 British tourists in
a horrific bus accident near Lydenburg, about 400 kilometers east
of Johannesburg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
