<HEADLINE> USA Beats South Korea 5-0 in U.S. Cup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- World Cup winner the United
States beat South Korea 5-0 in the opening game of the U.S. Cup
women's soccer tournament in Columbus, Ohio, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Brazil beat Finland 3-1 in the first of the
doubleheader.
</P>
<P>
Danielle Fotopoulos scored two late goals to wrap up the
shooting spree for the Americans, who beat China to win the World
Cup title this summer.
</P>
<P>
The victory was the 23rd of the year for the United States, and
the record for the team in the past five years is 101-8-8.
</P>
<P>
In front of 23,101 home fans, the U.S. team completely
dominated the court, outshooting their rivals 35-2, including 17-1
on goal.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Cindy Parlow opened the scoring in the 10th minute and
Mia Hamm made it 2-0 in the 36th minute. It was the 112th career
goal for Hamm, who injuryed last month.
</P>
<P>
Mibrett wound up the first half with another goal. Fotopoulos
found target twice in the 82nd minute and 90th minute.
</P>
<P>
The second round of the four-team tournament will be on
Thursday in Kansas City when Brazil plays South Korea and Finland
faces the United States. 
