<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Rice Exports Top A Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's rice exports topped a
record of 3.8 million tones in the first nine months, Vietnam's
English daily Vietnam News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The nine-month figure equaled last year's total rice exports,
an official of the Ministry of Trade (MoT) said.
</P>
<P>
The official optimistically said that the national target of
exporting 4.3 million tones of rice this year is "within reach".
</P>
<P>
He said that over 200,000 tones of rice a month could be
exported in each of the last three months of the year, with
250,000 tones likely to be exported in October alone, pushing
exports over the first 10 months to over 4 million tones.
</P>
<P>
This will represent a year-on-year rise of 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
A slight recovery in world rice prices means that exporters are
expecting higher earnings, although prices are still lower than
they were last year.
</P>
<P>
Asia still accounts for nearly 60 percent of Vietnam's rice
export markets, with Africa accounts for 20 percent, followed by
the Middle East for 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Europe and the America consume nine percent of Vietnam's rice
exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
