<HEADLINE> Toyota Produces 100 Millionth Vehicle in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The largest Japanese automaker
Toyota Motor Corp. produced its 100 millionth vehicle in Japan on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Toyota is the world's third automaker to achieve domestic
production of 100 million vehicles, following two major U.S.
automakers, General Motors Corp. and Ford Motor Co.
</P>
<P>
Toyota's 100 millionth car, a white Crown luxury passenger car,
was displayed with vintage models at a ceremony held at a plant in
Toyota, Aichi Prefecture, where the Japanese automaker bases its
headquarters, according to a media report.
</P>
<P>
Toyota started production in 1935 and made its 50 millionth
vehicle domestically in 1986. 
