<HEADLINE> Thai Canned Rice Becomes Emerging Star </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Exports for Thai canned rice
are believed to increase substantially, making the new processed
product become an emerging star in the international market in the
near future, according to a report of the Board of Investment of
Thailand (BOI) available here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The BOI had approved an investment promotion project, worth 18
million baht ( 0.45 million U.S. dollars) for a local producer of
Thai canned rice and other processed seasonings for Thai dishes.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Sudchitr Intarathaiwong, director of Investment Services
Center of the BOI was quoted as saying that the decision was aimed
at giving support for the producer to penetrate and expand the new
exports into the world market.
</P>
<P>
The firm had a total production capacity of 18,000 tones
annually, 90 percent of which would be exported, she said.
</P>
<P>
Exports under the producer's brand name, Khun Perm, include
Thai processed canned rice, Thai flied canned rice and processed
seasoning for such Thai famous dishes as Thai flied noodle, some
flied vegetables and Som Tam--sliced papaya with ground beans,
tomatoes and some spices.
</P>
<P>
Rice used in the products would mostly be famous Thai fragrant
rice, while some would be glutinous rice, said the official.
</P>
</TEXT>
