<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Seizes 102 Kilograms of Heroin at Border With Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian customs officers seized
102 kilograms of heroin at a check point bordering Turkey on
Sunday, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The customs authorities said that the narcotic drugs were found
in a Mercedes cargo van with Macedonian registration. The drugs
were contained in 200 packages among other goods such as sofas,
spring-beds and carpets originating from Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The driver, a Serb citizen aged about 30, had tried to escape
and was later detained by the border officers. He was found to
have a criminal record. 
