<HEADLINE> Northwest China to Condense Official Conferences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 4 (Xinhua)-- Northwest China's Shaanxi
Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) has
issued a strict regulation condensing official conferences so that
local leaders can engage in more practical work.
</P>
<P>
In the past, the schedule of local provincial leaders included
an overwhelming number of meetings, leaving them not enough time
to go deep into the grassroots.
</P>
<P>
To free officials from unnecessary and redundant businesses,
the provincial Party committee decided to take a number of
measures to simplify meeting procedures which will combine similar
meetings and eliminate unimportant ones.
</P>
<P>
The regulation also requires that provincial leaders to inspect
localities at all levels, but the places hosting them must do so
in a frugal manner, at low expense and with simplest receptions.
</P>
