<HEADLINE> China Wins 4 Titles In Dutch Badminton Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DEN BOSCH, Netherlands, October 3 (Xinhua) -- China won all but
one titles in the Holland Plaza Open '99 badminton grand prix in
the Southern Dutch city on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The women's singles produced the most spectacular final between
Chinese Tang Chunyu and Mia Audina of the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Tang, 20, who made her debut in the world arena, defeated
Audina 11-13, 11-4 and 11-7 after Audina, a former Indonesian
player, eliminated Tang's Chinese compatriot seventh-ranked Zhou
Mi, who was the top seed of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Both the men's singles and women's doubles became the all-
Chinese affairs.
</P>
<P>
Xia Xuanze, champion in the fourth Chinese City Games last
month, outwitted teammate Ji Xinpeng, top seed of the Dutch open,
15-10, 15-13, while Chen Lin and Jiang Xuelian defeated Zhou Mi
and Tang Chunyu 15-9, 15-4 to take the women's doubles title.
</P>
<P>
In the mixed doubles, China's Chen Qiqiu paired with Chen Lin
overcame Denmark's Martin L. Hansen and Pernille Harder with 15-11,
9-15 and 15-10.
</P>
<P>
The only title that slipped away from the Chinese players was
in the men's doubles, which was won by Choong Tan Fook and Lee Wan
Wah of Malaysia who defeated Lars Paaske and Martin L. Hansen of
Denmark 15-4, 6-15 and 15-9.
</P>
<P>
A total of 50,000 US dollars was put at stake for the top 16
players, with the men's single champion getting 4,000 and women's
singles champion pocketing 3,450.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese badminton team, which is the second-string squad in
the country, will try its best again later this month in the
German open and the Danish open. 
</P>
