<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- In a family final, Serena
Williams defeated her older sister Venus for the first time to
take the women's singles title at the Grand Slam Cup in Munich,
Germany on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Serena, the US Open champion, outwitted the defending champion
Venus 6-1, 3-6 and 6-3 for a 900,000 US dollars payday.
</P>
<P>
