<HEADLINE> Indonesian Assembly Elects New Chairman, Vice Chairmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's highest
decision-making body, the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR),
elected new leadership here on Sunday midnight.
</P>
<P>
Amien Rais, general chairman of the National Mandate Party, get
305 votes, defeating his nearest rival Matori Abdul Djalil,
general chairman of the National Awakening Party, which get 279
votes.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Matori and other six candidates had became the
Vice Chairmen of the MPR.
</P>
<P>
The other six vice chairmen are: Kwik Kian Gie from the
Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle, Ginanjar Kartasasmita
from the Golkar Party, Hari Sabarno from the Indonesian Military,
Yusuf Amir Faisal from the Crescent Star Party, Nasri Adlani from
the interest group representatives faction and Husni Thamrin from
the United Development Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
