<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Finland 3-1 in U.S. Cup Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- World Cup bronze medal
winning team Brazil beat Finland 3-1 to win the opening match of
the U.S. Cup women's soccer tournament Sunday in Columbus, Ohio,
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Roseli scored two goals and assisted another in the game. She
opened the scoring in the dying minute of the first half with a
long shot over the head of goalkeeper Satu Kunnas.
</P>
<P>
Roseli found the target again in the 78th minute again. The
Brazlians outshot Finland 30-6 throughout.
</P>
<P>
The second round of the tournament will be at Kansas City,
Missouri, on Thursday when Brazil plays South Korea and Finland
faces the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
